# 🖥 Local Development with Minikube

### Start the cluster:

minikube start --driver=docker

### Enable Ingress:

minikube addons enable ingress

### Verify controller:

kubectl get pods -n ingress-nginx


## 🌐 External Access (Ingress + Minikube)

minikube tunnel

---

## 🔄 Automatic Retraining

The breast-cancer-retrain CronJob runs the training on a schedule.

Each execution:

1. Creates a new Pod using the training image
2. Loads configuration from ConfigMaps and Secrets
3. Trains the model
4. Stores it in the persistent volume (model-pvc)
5. Terminates automatically after completion

This ensures the model is continuously updated without manual intervention.
---

## 📜 Deployment Script

Trigger deployment updates with:

./scripts/deploy.sh [<TAG>]

If <TAG> is omitted, the current Git commit SHA is used.

This script: 

- Deploys or updates the application using Helm.

- Updates container images.

- Applies all Kubernetes resources

---

## 🧪 Testing

The test/ folder includes:

- upload_csv.py – Upload CSV files
- insert_training.py – Insert training records
- test_predict.py – Test prediction endpoint
- concurrent_stress_test.py – Stress test API

### Example
python test/test_predict.py

--- 

## 🛠 CI/CD with GitHub Actions

- Builds and pushes all images on push to main
- Tags images with commit SHA (immutable versioning)
- Deploys automatically using Helm
- Injects secrets securely via GitHub Actions Secrets

---

## 📎 Notes

This project is designed to run:

- Locally using Minikube (development)
- On remote Kubernetes clusters (production-ready structure)
The original dataset has been replaced with a synthetic dataset to preserve privacy and confidentiality.  
No personally identifiable information (PII) is included, ensuring compliance with data protection best practices.